STORMIN ATTILA ran at the back of the pack then coming down the stretch impeded the path of STACKERS causing loss of positioning. SECOND BATTALION ran evenly throughout the race. THERE WAS A STEWARDS INQUIRY ON STORMIN ATTILA, IT WAS DETERMINED THAT STORMIN ATTILA IMPEDED STACKERS MID STRETCH CAUSING THE LOSS OF PLACEMENT. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 16500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. New Mexico Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOOIT ran off pace from the leaders then coming down the stretch made a move in the middle of the track to over take the leaders. BELLA Y SOFIA ran in the two path then coming down the stretch went to the outside and followed DOOIT to the wire. CHOCOLATE FRECKLES pressed the pace of BLUE COWGIRL and eventually wore her down to pass on in the middle of the stretch. BLUE COWGIRL had good early speed then in the middle of the stretch CHOCOLATE FRECKLES caught and passed with a half furlong left. HEMATITE started out in the front of the pack then as the race went on slowly shuffled back throughout. DOM PROUD started out in the middle of the pack then fell to the back but coming down the stretch made up some ground with a late bid. MOBILEAGILEHOSTILE stayed on the outside went wide into the turn and coming out of it, had a late interest coming down the stretch. SIMPERING SMILE was off pace from the leaders then coming out of the turn and into the stretch started to fade. MISS JAX ran at the back of the pack then at the coming down late stretch passed the tired foes. MISS CONTINENTAL started at the front of the pack then as the race went on fell back. SPICEY SECRET ran with no menace passing a tired foe at the end. EMMYS SILVER had a mild gain early then flattened out in the middle of the turn and got passed by remaining foes. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.
